race.comment: BAILS (3) is a promising mare in the Matt Dunn yard. Just missed on debut and then stepped up to 1800m at the Gold Coast and won her Maiden comfortably as expected. The extra 200m will hold no fears and she benefits from Newman's 1.5kg claim. Maps well and can round out a successful day for the stable. BRAIN WAVE (4) just missed at Ballina as a firm favourite over 1920m. She likes to run along, and Mallyon is a positive jockey engagement. In good hands and should be right in it. PERRI LASS (7) brings strong provincial form over a mile and has placed at this course/trip. She's also going well enough to feature. AYASAKI (1) presents off a narrow defeat at Beaudesert over a staying trip. He led in that but is likely to take a sit today dropping back to a middle distance. This is harder, but he'll be around the mark.
